<HEAD>Pop Star Cancels Two Concerts Because of Swollen Vocal Chords</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pop superstar Michael Jackson canceled a
sold-out performance shortly before he was supposed to take the
stage Monday night because of swollen vocal chords, his publicist
said.
   The decision, announced about 40 minutes before the start of the
show, was made on advice of the singer's physician, publicist Lee
Solters said.
   Tuesday's sold-out performance also was canceled, and both will
be rescheduled at a later date, Solters said.
   An estimated 30,000 ticketholders at the Sports Arena were told
to save their stubs for admission to the new shows, Solters said.
   Jackson began a six-concert engagement Sunday night as part of
his worldwide tour promoting his ``Bad'' album.
   Concerts on Nov. 20, 21, and 22 will go on as scheduled, Solters
said.
</TEXT>
