his Senate seat in time to give his successor a jump in seniority
over the new class of lawmakers being sworn in Jan. 3. Quayle said
he had ``no recommendations'' to make on a successor when he met
privately with Indiana Gov. Robert Orr, who will make the
appointment.
   _The next chairman of the House Budget Committee said tax
increases will be needed next year to make legally required cuts in
the deficit. ``Anybody who's dealt with budget issues knows the size
of the challenge is too large to exempt any areas,'' said Rep. Leon
Panetta, D-Calif.
