<DATELINE>PALM SPRINGS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sonny Bono's face once apppeared on
record album covers and the TV show he shared with former wife Cher,
but now he's putting it on the line to help this desert resort
city's budget.
   The city, facing a $2.3 million budget deficit, is selling
T-shirts bearing the first-term mayor's likeness.
   Two versions are available. One says ``I Want You Babe'' and
shows Bono holding a tennis racket. The other implores: ``Meet Me in
Palm Springs,'' and shows Bono driving a vintage car.
