<2ND_LINE>AM-Malaysia-Space,0118</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Malaysia Studying Whether to Participate in Soviet Space Program</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Soviet-Shuttle, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Malaysia is studying whether to
participate in the Soviet Union's space program, a move that would
cost $10 million, a government official said Tuesday.
   Considering the cost, Science, Technology and Environment
Minister Amar Stephen Yong said the matter needed further study, as
well as Cabinet approval.
   There are 22 Malaysian applicants to fly in space, and four would
be selected for further training to become a cosmonaut, he said.
   ``We have to ascertain whether our participation in the program
would benefit the nation in any way and therefore a detailed study
was necessary,'' he said.
</TEXT>
