<HEAD>When JFK Was Shot: Senators, Stars Recall Where they Were</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: A retransmission of one in a package of stories for the
Kennedy assassination anniversary originally for release on the
weekend of Nov. 4-6.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Where were you, and what was your reaction when
you heard that President John F. Kennedy had been shot?''
   John Jovich, who was 8 years old when he overheard the school
principal whisper news of the shooting to his teacher, recently put
that question to 250 celebrities and assembled their responses into
a book, ``Reflections on JFK's Assassination,'' published by
Woodbine House.
   Sen. Daniel Inouye, D-Hawaii, recalled being near the Senate
chambers and realizing that Sen. Edward Kennedy, D-Mass., was the
presiding officer. ``I immediately dispatched a page to tell Senator
Kennedy to leave the rostrum for a matter of utmost emergency. It
was then that Senator Kennedy learned of his brother's shooting.''
   Singer Billy Joel said he first tried to console an eighth-grade
classmate who was crying. He later took a long walk, feeling ``a
deep bitterness and a despair I had never before experienced in my
life.''
   Rona Barrett, the Hollywood columnist, remembers being ``at a
famous Palm Springs racquet club. People came running out of the
clubhouse screaming that someone had shot Jack Kennedy.''
   Roy Rogers said the assassination ``proved to me that we have a
lot more subversive activists in our country than we realize.''
   Former President Jimmy Carter said he had walked into his
warehouse to weigh a load of grain when a group of farmers told him
of the shooting. He said he prayed, and ``wept openly for the first
time in 10 years _ for the first time since the day my own father
died.''
   Novelist Isaac Asimov said all he could think about was ``that I
didn't want Johnson. But I got him.''
   Burt Bacharach said he was working on a song with Hal David when
he found out about the shooting. He said he left the building and
went to a bar, where he eventually got ``into a fight with some
people who were having a good time laughing, etc., totally
disrespectful of the moment.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Use Anytime</NOTE>
