<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Honda,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Japanese Auto Makers Report First-half Results</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   TOKYO (AP) Honda Motor Co. reported Tuesday its earnings rose
11.4 percent in the first half ended as its sales rose nearly 10
percent.
   Because of a change in Honda's fiscal year, the comparison was
made with hypothetical six-month figures obtained by prorating
results in the transitional seven-month, year-earlier first half.
   Honda's earnings rose to 48.537 billion yen, or $392.9 million,
from an adjusted 43.572 billion yen a year earlier. That translates
to 49.06 yen, against an adjusted 43.50 yen.
   Sales totaled 1.674 trillion yen, up 9.8 percent from adjusted
sales of 1.524 trillion yen.
   Officials at Honda, a leading Japanese manufacturer of
motorcycles and four-wheel vehicles, attributed the sales gain to
favorable car sales in Japan, the United States and certain other
overseas markets.
</TEXT>
