<HEAD>Minnesota Mining To Repurchase Additional Shares of Its Common
Stock</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPLEWOOD, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Minnesota Mining and Manufacturing Co.
said Tuesday its board of directors has authorized the repurchase of
up to 10 million additional shares of its common stock by May 31,
1989.
   The purchases are an extension of a continuing program to
re-acquire shares for employee stock-purchase and savings plans and
for other corporate purposes, the company said.
   The action brings to 14 million the number of shares authorized
for purchase through next May. Of this number, about two million
shares have been purchased since June 1 of this year, the company
said.
   Minnesota Mining had 226.2 million shares outstanding as of Oct.
31.
