<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru f0032 11-15 0140</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0032,0147</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares Up</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices drifted higher Tuesday in uninspired
dealings on the London Stock Exchange.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 8 points,
or 0.4 percent, to 1,802.3.
   Volume was 341.8 million shares, compared with the 479.9 million
shares traded Monday.
   Some selected shares were energized by takeover talk, dealers
said, but added that they saw few substantive moves in prices.
   ``Institutions are still out of the game and without them, we
can't expect to cover much territory,'' one trader said.
   Dealers said they were encouraged by the fact that the index
managed to close above the psychologically important 1,800 level.
   The narrower Financial Times 30-share index edged up 8.4 points
to 1,460.9.
   The Financial Times 500-share index rose 4.16 points to 1,026.11.
</TEXT>
